# IS2568 Artificial Intelligence Project

## Project Title
Artificial Intelligence Web Application for Prediction and Detection Tasks

## Live Application
🔗 https://isaiproject-idnqfgic6apptsazypebxhe.streamlit.app/

## Source Code Repository
🔗 https://github.com/6704062611310/IS_AI_Project

---

## 1. Introduction
This project is developed as part of the **IS2568 Artificial Intelligence** course.  
The objective of this project is to demonstrate the application of Artificial Intelligence techniques through a web-based system.

The system integrates both:
- Machine Learning (ML)
- Deep Learning (DL)

to solve real-world problems in prediction and image classification.

---

## 2. Objectives
- To design and develop an AI-based web application
- To apply Machine Learning techniques for prediction tasks
- To implement Deep Learning models for image classification
- To provide a user-friendly interface using Streamlit

---

## 3. System Overview
The application consists of two main modules:

### 3.1 Football Match Prediction
This module predicts the outcome of football matches using Ensemble Learning techniques.

**Algorithms used:**
- Random Forest
- Gradient Boosting
- Voting Classifier

**Functionality:**
- Input match-related data
- Predict match outcome
- Display prediction results to users

---

### 3.2 Weapon Detection
This module detects weapons from images using Deep Learning.

**Techniques used:**
- MobileNetV2 (Pre-trained model)
- Transfer Learning
- Fine-tuning

**Functionality:**
- Upload image
- Analyze image content
- Classify whether a weapon is present

---

## 4. System Architecture
The system is implemented as a web application using Streamlit and follows a simple architecture:

- Frontend: Streamlit Interface
- Backend: Python-based AI models
- Model Layer: Machine Learning & Deep Learning models

---

## 5. Tools and Technologies
- Python
- Streamlit
- Scikit-learn
- TensorFlow / Keras
- MobileNetV2

---

